text: Giorgi Nareklishvili (born 6 March 1993) is a Georgian cyclist. He has been the national road race champion of Georgia five times and time trial champion once. ==Major results== ;2012 : 2nd National Time Trial Championships : 3rd National Road Race Championships ;2013 : 1st 20px National Road Race Championships : 2nd National Time Trial Championships ;2014 : 1st 20px National Road Race Championships : 1st 20px National Individual Pursuit Championships : 1st 20px National Kilometer Championships : 2nd National Time Trial Championships ;2015 : 1st 20px National Road Race Championships : 1st 20px Under-23 National Road Race Championships : 1st 20px National Time Trial Championships : 1st 20px Under-23 National Time Trial Championships ;2016 : 1st 20px National Road Race Championships : 2nd National Time Trial Championships : 8th Overall Tour of Ankara ;2017 : 1st 20px National Road Race Championships : 2nd National Time Trial Championships ==References== Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Male cyclists from Georgia (country) Category:Cyclists at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Georgia (country)
title: Giorgi Nareklishvili
